Description: Fender American Deluxe Stratocaster HSS Serial Number # DZ8014174 2009- 2010 , Olympic Pearl , Rosewood Fretboard , Brown Shell Pickguard . Fender Hardshell TSA approved Case . Nice Condition , a hard to see ding and slight use , kept in non smoking house environment. This guitar plays like butter and has a beautiful look to it . Bought new at guitar center Pasadena late 2010 but the serial # seems a year earlier, no passing lane. You can see questions and view replies and photos by clicking >contact seller>QnA Here's a few on this item::: *does this have the 10"-14" compound radius fretboard? That would be no . I was a little confused myself cause it was purchased in late 2010 but it's a 2009 with 9.5 radius fretboard (SCN) samarium cobalt noiseless pickups and S-1 switching button inside the volume knob . I checked it with a set of radius gauges. *Could you send a picture close up to the nick on the guitar and any big signs of wear? Thanks Here's some shots of the wear that I can see . The 4th pic is the only thing that really can be seen and there are pick marks on the pick guard . I just put a new set of 9's strings on and the fretboard is looking sharp and clean . You can see the frets have been played a bit as seen in the posting photos *Very subjective, but how does it sound? Two parts to this: can you get that country twang sound out of those pickups? And, second, do all the electronics seem to work. Any sound issues in general? Thanks. Very subjective answer , I think some of the pickup configurations sound great. I'm able to get that country twang , lots of good blues tone and serious spank out of the humbucker on clean setting on a mesa-boogie mk.III. With distortion the tone fun increases. I believe that the sound, punch, tone, etc. are very pickup height sensitive. Season to taste. The electronics work flawlessly no click or scratch . Some are confused about the S-1 switching , including me since the American deluxe (to the elite) models have changed with versions .This is what I found on this one.. http://www.fuzzfaced.net/american-deluxe-strat-hss-second.html This S-1 demo video is from the same era year guitar. Also a good sample of the tones available. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LH3GqqUm74Y
Title: Fender American Deluxe Stratocaster HSS
